-- V0.2 OBSERVATIONS
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

⊢= obs-guard-skip-mechanics
  given §29-bootstrapper
  yield observations ≡ "GUARD CLAUSE IN ACTION: The v0.2 guard on spawn-gap-fillers (`given is-complete where is-complete = false`) demonstrates conditional spawning. In iteration 1, is-complete = false → guard TRUE → spawner fires 3 gap-fillers. In iteration 2, is-complete = true → guard FALSE → spawner SKIPPED → yields ⊥. This is precisely the pattern that v0.1 could not express cleanly. Without guards, spawn-gap-fillers would fire with an empty gaps list, spawning zero cells but still consuming an LLM call for the spawner evaluation. The guard avoids even that overhead."

⊢= obs-given-optional-bottom-path
  given §29-bootstrapper
  yield observations ≡ "GIVEN? + ⊥ PROPAGATION PATH: When spawn-gap-fillers is guard-skipped, its yields (§gap-filler-cells[]) become ⊥. No gap-filler cells are spawned. The wildcards gap-filler-*→additional-findings and gap-filler-*→patch-recommendations match NOTHING (empty array, not ⊥ — wildcards on zero matches return []). But re-synthesize uses given? for these wildcards, so it accepts the empty arrays and passes through the revised-plan unchanged. This is the correct behavior: given? + wildcard + guard-skip = clean no-op path. The v0.2 features compose well."

⊢= obs-accumulate-vs-replace
  given §29-bootstrapper
  yield observations ≡ "ACCUMULATE MODE JUSTIFIED: This program uses `accumulate` (the default) for both spawners, unlike program 01 which uses `replace`. The difference is semantic: in program 01, each ⊢∘ iteration produces entirely new hypotheses that invalidate previous experiments. In program 29, specialists persist across iterations — the gap-fillers ADD to the knowledge base rather than replacing it. Accumulate means specialist-{0,1,2,3} and gap-filler-{0,1,2} all coexist at quiescence. The wildcards gather from the full set. This is the right choice: gap-fillers refine the plan, they don't replace the original specialist knowledge."

⊢= obs-aspirational-oracle-effect
  given §29-bootstrapper
  yield observations ≡ "ASPIRATIONAL ORACLES (v0.2): synthesize and evaluate-completeness are ⊢∘-managed, so their ⊨ assertions are aspirational — they provide feedback but don't independently block freezing. In this execution, all aspirational oracles passed anyway (the LLM produced good output). The aspirational designation matters for the FAILURE case: if synthesize's oracle 'draft-plan includes at least 3 ramen spots' had failed in iteration 1, the cell would still freeze (because ⊢∘ controls freezing), the failure message would feed into the through chain, and the evolution loop would improve the output. Without aspirational semantics, the oracle failure would trigger ⊨? retry (wasting 3 attempts) before the ⊢∘ loop even gets a chance to iterate."

⊢= obs-bootstrap-convergence-depth
  given §29-bootstrapper
  yield observations ≡ "CONVERGENCE IN TWO ITERATIONS: Like program 01, this program converges in 2 ⊢∘ iterations (quality 5 → 8). The pattern is consistent: iteration 1 produces a reasonable first draft with identifiable gaps; iteration 2 fills those gaps and crosses the quality threshold. The bootstrapper's 80/20 structure is revealing — 4 specialist cells produce 80% of the plan quality, 3 gap-fillers provide the remaining 20% (precision details like specific shop names, hours, budget). This suggests that zero-start bootstrapping has a natural two-phase structure: BREADTH (specialist wave) → DEPTH (gap-filler wave), and that more than 2 ⊢∘ iterations yield diminishing returns for planning tasks."

⊢= obs-seven-spawned-from-nothing
  given §29-bootstrapper
  yield observations ≡ "SEVEN FROM ZERO: The program starts with zero domain-specific cells and spawns 7 (4 specialists + 3 gap-fillers). The meta-cell (analyze-needs) decided the SHAPE of the solution — what kinds of knowledge were needed — and the spawners materialized that shape into concrete cells. This is Cell's metacircular bootstrap in miniature: the program reasons about what program to build, builds it, evaluates it, extends it, and converges. The final output (a polished Tokyo itinerary) is produced by an ensemble that didn't exist at program start. Cell didn't just execute a plan — it invented the plan for how to plan."
